# Local development environment variables for Metro (`expo start --dev-client`).
#
# Why these are committed:
#   - The Supabase URL is the project's public endpoint -- not a secret.
#   - The "publishable" key (sb_publishable_*) is designed to ship in
#     client apps publicly. Row-level security (RLS) is what protects
#     the data, not key secrecy.
#   - Apple/Google ship the same value inside every installed binary.
#     Hiding it from the repo gives no security benefit while making
#     onboarding for new developers (and the operator's own machine
#     setup) needlessly fragile.
#
# Anything ACTUALLY secret (e.g. service_role keys, Sentry auth tokens
# used during builds) lives in EAS secrets and never in this file.
#
# Build profiles in eas.json carry the same values inline so EAS Build
# is unaffected if this file ever drifts; this file is just for Metro.
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://dxahcamntwtuzftxbxgx.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_mpxg4esDmwVJ6CkJTTJ6CA__-6QrZqJ
EXPO_PUBLIC_ENV=development
